---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { CONTACT } from "../config";
---

<Base
  title="About QuantumSOP"
  description="QuantumSOP builds conservative, defensible AI and post-quantum compliance documentation for government contractors — founded by a practitioner from the federal and state compliance world."
  docId="QSOP-WEB-006"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Built by someone who has sat on your side of the questionnaire.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        QuantumSOP was founded on a practitioner's background in federal and state
        compliance and grants administration — the world where documentation either
        holds up under review or it doesn't.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Why this exists</h2>
      <p>
        In 2026, AI-use questions and quantum-readiness questions started appearing in
        the same solicitations. Small and mid-sized vendors face the same documentation
        expectations as primes — without the compliance departments. The alternatives
        are five-figure consulting engagements or improvising under deadline.
      </p>
      <p>
        QuantumSOP is the third option: conservative, procurement-tested documentation
        with transparent version control, priced below most micro-purchase thresholds.
      </p>
      <h2>The operating principles</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Transparency first.</strong> Every template change is documented on the public <a href="/changelog">changelog</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Conservative and defensible.</strong> Accuracy over speed; expert review before ambition.</li>
        <li><strong>Evidence-oriented.</strong> Every document exists because a reviewer asks a specific question.</li>
        <li><strong>Honest boundaries.</strong> We tell you what the Kit doesn't do, and when you don't need more.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Questions? <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT}`}>{CONTACT}</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
